The steady-state and delayed emission spectra of the B-CDs@SiO2 composite exhibit excitation-dependent features (Fig. 3
                     ). The B-CDs@SiO2 composite demonstrates highly tunable emission, which gradually red-shifts from 470 nm to 580 nm as the excitation wavelength changes from 260 nm to 500 nm (Fig. 3b to 3d). The afterglow color shifts from blue under 254 nm excitation to white under 365 nm excitation, to green under 395 nm excitation, and to yellow under white light excitation. Additionally, time-dependent color evolution is observed in the persistent luminescence excited by 254 nm and 310 nm (Fig. 4
                     g). After ceasing 254 nm excitation, the afterglow color of the B-CDs@SiO2 composite transitions from yellowish-green to green, then to sky-blue, and finally to blue (Fig. 4).
